The Chris Hani Baragwanath Academic Hospital in Johannesburg has come under fire for the cancellation of nearly 9-hundred surgical operations this year alone. That is a significant and alarming number. DA's Jack Bloom has slammed the hospital, saying it's causing patients more distress. eNCA speaks to Bloom for more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The DA's Jack Bloom says the cancellation of surgical operations at the Chris Hani Baragwanath Hospital in Johannesburg could have easily been prevented. Gauteng Health MEC Nomathemba Mokgethi confirmed that 870 operations were cancelled at the hospital this year alone. She attributes this to broken laundry machines and infrastructure challenges. READ:Â DA: Chris Hani Hospital not the only one with food shortages "One of the preventable factors which I feel strongly about because of lack of clean linen," Bloom said. "This is very simple to arrange. How come after so many years so many hospitals have had to cancel operations and patients go without clean linen? "So the MEC confirmed that laundry problems were behind a lot of cancellations, honestly the simple solution to buy from private laundries, we wouldn't have all this."